  SQL Basics: Data Retrieval - Single Table
Retrieve data using text query (SELECT, WHERE, DISTINCT, LIKE)
SELECT, FROM, and WHERE are the basic SQL functions.
SELECT * (select all columns of a database.)
USE function - the query to use a particular database
COUNT function - numerical count of rows.
DISTINCT function - see the unique values present in a given column.
'%’ - wild card search.
LIKE function and ‘%’ -   filter the rows based on a text value.

